king tinsel ribbons and braid.  Jewish, had to emigrate in Nazi period.  His brother in America, but father Anglophile, so came to England September 1939.  Had already ordered new ribbon-making looms from Swiss factory to be sent to England.  Difficult to
 secure visa, but succeeded with help of author barrister cousin Bechhofer-Roberts.  This cousin and a business friend in Nottingham also lent money, started his own reasonably prosperous small new tinsel ribbon factory in Nottingham, where Frank}{
