?  The business was part and parcel of daily life, mother did the accounts, as children visited factory - still knows about weaving ribbons, and still finds finance easy to handle.  Has run a theatre company for years without losing money.
\par 
\par Nottingham High School, highly academic, on a scholarship.  High-powered physics teacher.  Reproducing the Millikan experiment.  Learning how to build equipment.  Creating a mirage.  Engl
ish teacher gave him a lasting love of theatre -  cannot write plays, but enjoys directing them.  French also well taught.  Left in 1954, with entrance to Cambridge to read mathematics.
\par 
\par Home culture Middle European.  Much of the furniture brought over by 
