though maybe wrongly, for his American cousin was a distinguished statistician, son a mathematician), so read mechanical sciences.  A very theoretical approach to engineering, a lot of lectures, practical, supervisions, found civil engineering quite inter
esting, but not inspired to work very hard.  Students work harder today.  Did a lot of theatre, could have become an actor or director - many good people in Cambridge then.  Ran a theatre company in the summers.
