\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid11301916\charrsid2513566 PhD}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12397272\charrsid2513566 .  So in one bound, he became a s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid11415128 ociologist}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12397272\charrsid2513566 , sharing an office with Jennifer Platt.

\par 
\par Liked David Lockwood instantly, and still a very close friend, as Jean is with Leonore.  Both David a
nd he smoked pipes, infuriating Jennifer.  David was a Lecturer on the Faculty.  Moody, but fun.  Tenaciously tests ideas, in ways which people find provocative, but Frank finds}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid11415128  it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12397272\charrsid2513566  amusing.  Hit it off as two families.
\par  
\par Jennifer Platt had done a degree in English Literature before her Chicago MA, where she learnt some survey sociology.  She and Frank very different.  She had read a lot of sociology.
\par 
\par Best legacy of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12397272\charrsid2513566 The Affluent Worker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12397272\charrsid2513566  was its research design, brilliant, a
 permanent influence on him; its worst legacy `embourgeoisement' as a word.  Also learnt how difficult it is to design a good questionnaire.  The plan of testing the locale most favourable to the thesis was already divided by John and David.  Worked as a 
t
eam, decisions collegiate, often after furious debate.  Met regularly in David's office.  Frank and Jennifer ran the interview programmes, starting with all the work interviews, because he knew about the sociology of work.  John and Frank provided the ind
ustrial input, John then more of an industrial sociologist, David the real sociologist of class, had written }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12397272\charrsid2513566 The Black-Coated Worker}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12397272\charrsid2513566 . 
\par  
\par Frank mugging up sociology, doing some supervision in sociology (and also in maths), trying to learn faster than the students.
\par 
\par Michael Rose, trained as anthropologist, hired to work with Frank on the industrial interviews.  Problem of dealing with union opposition to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid9976611  the research at Skefk
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12397272\charrsid2513566 o, had to go drinking with shop stewards, and then make a speech to their meeting.  Le
arnt a lot about social research very fast, you had to be quick on your feet.  Jennifer mainly responsible for the household interviews.
\par 
\par Steam technology, questionnaires transferred to coding sheets, key punched by punch girls, al}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7241315 l in-house.  Meetings to decide}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12397272\charrsid2513566  how to code the unstructured questions.  Counter-sorter in the basement.   Hand calculator.  Analysing was fun, intellectually fascinating.
\par 
\par John did some of the industrial interviewing, which he enjoyed.  Frank and John did most of the Vauxhall interviews before Michael came. 
\par  
\par Because every question had a clear purpose, the interpretation did not need to emerge - they knew where they were going.  But the idea of orientation to work became more important as they analysed the industrial data.  Joh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid2647390 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12397272\charrsid2513566  
was the prime mover in this, influenced by French sociology, especially Alfred Villinor, Touraine.  But no questions originally designed to measure work orientation: would have needed, more of a psychology battery of questions.  The industrial volume not 
part of the original plan.  John  decided on it when he began to analyse the data.  That was John's prime contribution.
\par Coding of household volume much more difficult, much time working out by hand how to code friendship and kinship.
\par 
\par David Lockwood had the idea of the political volume, crystal limpidity, tells a story clearly.  He had the ideas, and Frank discussed and did the analysis on the counter-sorter.
\par 
\par The project ended in 1964-5.  Jennifer went to Sussex.  Frank stayed on in Ca
mbridge, paid to work on project, and doing a little on his thesis.  But increasingly dissatisfied with Cambridge, its sense of being centre of the universe, the minor role of sociology.  The faculty had excellent people, including Dorothy Wedderburn, Rob
in Matthews (with whom played chess), famous economists.  But Cambridge people just not interested in sociology.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12397272 
