nd, used modelling to discover why people go into small shops as the failure rate is so high: discovered that there is a group of new people constantly coming in and dropping out, but there's also a sizable group who go on for years.  Surveys had not been
 as common in social research as is often thought.  Some things can only be done by surveys.  The survey was again run in-house, as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12397272\charrsid2513566 
Affluent Worker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid12397272\charrsid2513566 , with similar team meetings and debates.  Research officers Richard Bland and Veronica Rushforth.  Looked aft
er interviewers, checked interviews, coded, punched, analysed in-house, no agency involved.  Believes in teamwork, treating your researchers as equals, encouraging their initiatives.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
